    "generated": "The activity \"Daily monitoring of network availability and network failures\" belongs to **operational monitoring** within the **operational management of information systems**.\n\n**Scope and tasks:**\n\n- **Scope:** Operational management of information systems  \n- **Task:** Monitoring\n\n**Explanation:**\n\nOperational management is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of all components of the information system, including the physical data processing systems and communication networks. Daily monitoring of network availability and network failures is a continuous activity that checks the proper working and effectiveness of the network infrastructure, which is critical for physical interoperability and integration of the health information system.\n\nThis monitoring helps to detect disruptions early, supports prompt incident handling, and minimizes downtime, thus maintaining the availability and reliability of health information systems.\n\nThis classification aligns with the example answer provided in Exercise 4.9.1 of the book.",
